title: Travel doctor: We want to make the most of our trip to West Australia
text:
Jim Jim Falls and creek in Kakadu National Park, Australia Getty Images Julia Brookes Published at 12:01AM, August 15 2015 
Q: I have been invited to a family wedding in New Zealand in late February but before the event I would like to do the Perth to Darwin coast of Australia, visiting some of the more outstanding natural sites such as the stromatolites in Shark Bay. All the tours I can find are either five-star luxury or basic, sleep under stars in the back of a four-wheel-drive. Iâ€™m looking for something in between. Keith Heazle, via email 
A The trip from Perth to Darwin is an incredible journey, with highlights including Pinnacles Desert, Kalbarri National Park, Shark Bay, Coral Bay, Ningaloo Subscribe now
